                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12849717" author="drwoods" created="Thu, 25 Mar 2010 15:00:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tests to verify any code changes fix the reported problem by allowing prior proxy behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12850109" author="drwoods" created="Fri, 26 Mar 2010 12:21:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patches to fix test failure when run with other tests due to entity/table name collisions.&lt;br/&gt;
Already checked into trunk as 927506 and 2.0.x as r927521.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12850112" author="drwoods" created="Fri, 26 Mar 2010 12:22:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Version of tests for 1.2.x showing expected behavior for 1.0 apps.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12850569" author="drwoods" created="Sat, 27 Mar 2010 20:25:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patches that add a new openjpa.Compatibility flag of IgnoreDetachedStateFieldForProxySerialization, which when 2.0 apps set to TRUE, will use the old 1.0 behavior for Proxies.writeReplace(), along with automatically using the old behavior for 1.0 apps.&lt;br/&gt;
Patch file 20100327 reverts a previous addition of removing proxies when they are detached, which broke a detach/merge scenario when using proxied List collections.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12850577" author="drwoods" created="Sat, 27 Mar 2010 20:54:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;compat+20100327 patches ported from trunk and combined into one patch and committed as r928271&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12851025" author="drwoods" created="Mon, 29 Mar 2010 18:59:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Doc updates for new Compatibility option.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12852222" author="drwoods" created="Thu, 1 Apr 2010 03:25:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Add Compatibility option to use new 2.0 behavior of removing proxy classes unless DetachedStateField=true, but default is still the old behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12853396" author="drwoods" created="Mon, 5 Apr 2010 16:12:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Update to 1.3.x docs to mention $proxy problem during serialization and how to use the new compatibility property.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12853411" author="drwoods" created="Mon, 5 Apr 2010 16:48:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that adds the openjpa.Compatibility property and behavior for IgnoreDetachedStateFieldForProxySerialization, along with doc and test updates.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12853422" author="drwoods" created="Mon, 5 Apr 2010 17:24:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Default behavior updated in 2.0.  Prior 1.3.x requires usage of Compatibility property to use the new behavior.  Patch attached for 1.2.x if we ever decide to apply it there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
